 1→//! # falcon-rs
 2→//!
 3→//! Rust implementation of the Falcon-512 post-quantum digital signature scheme.
 4→//!
 5→//! ## Quick Start
 6→//!
 7→//! ```rust,ignore
 8→//! use falcon_rs::falcon::Falcon;
 9→//! use falcon_rs::hash_to_point::Shake256Hash;
10→//!
11→//! // Generate keypair
12→//! let falcon = Falcon::<Shake256Hash>::new();
13→//! let (sk, vk) = falcon.keygen();
14→//!
15→//! // Sign and verify
16→//! let msg = b"Hello!";
17→//! let sig = sk.sign(msg);
18→//! assert!(vk.verify::<Shake256Hash>(msg, &sig).unwrap());
19→//! ```
20→//!
21→//! ## Features
22→//!
23→//! - `shake` - Enable SHAKE256 hash function (default)
24→//! - `wasm` - Enable WebAssembly bindings
25→//!
26→//! ## ⚠️ Security Warning
27→//!
28→//! This implementation is **NOT side-channel resistant**. It is ported from
29→//! the reference implementation which prioritizes correctness over constant-time
30→//! execution. Do not use in production environments where timing attacks are
31→//! a concern.
32→
